reviews.text: Usually 丼丼屋is pretty average, but when i came to this diamond hill one and ordered the 親子 don it was surprisingly good. The sauce and egg mixed together were wonderful and the chicken is soft and juicy. Also ordered the egg roll and it was rich in flavour with right amount of cheese on it.
Food variety is big! Good service and delicious food! Price a bit in higher side though.
It's suitable for dinner even you are alone. The taste is quite good but relatively salty. At dinner time, you may need to wait for a long time as it is crowded for people.
Ok lunch. Need improvement on the cher skill. Taste terrible actually. Don't mean to sound rude, but it is terrible food.
Alright place for a casual lunch or an afternoon tea.
